        <heading>5052.  Unambiguous language not to be disregarded</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 5052.  Unambiguous language not to be disregarded
When the language of an article is clear and free from ambiguity, its letter is not to be disregarded under the pretext of pursuing its spirit.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
